  "stimulus": null,
  "stem": "<p>Line <em>m</em> is defined by y = 3x + 2. Line <em>n</em> is parallel to line <em>m</em> in the <em>xy</em>-plane and passes through the point (0, 7). Which equation defines line <em>n</em>?</p>",
  "answerOptions": [
    {
      "id": "a",
      "content": "<p>y = -3x + 7</p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "b",
      "content": "<p>y = 3x + 7</p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "c",
      "content": "<p>y = 2x + 7</p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "d",
      "content": "<p>y = -2x + 7</p>"
    }
  ],
  "keys": [
    "b"
  ],
  "rationale": "<p>Choice B is correct. Parallel lines have equal slopes. Line m has slope 3, so line n also has slope 3. The point (0, 7) is the y-intercept, so b = 7. Therefore line n is y = 3x + 7.</p>",
